# Next.js app & components

## App Router

- Routes under `src/app/`. Payload admin routes live under `src/app/(payload)/`—treat as framework-owned; change only with care.
- Prefer **Server Components** by default. Add `'use client'` only for interactivity, hooks, or browser APIs.
- Keep data fetching in server components or route handlers; pass serializable props to clients.

## UI

- Reuse `src/components/ui/*` (shadcn). Keep Tailwind classes consistent with surrounding components.
- For auth-sensitive UI, follow existing patterns (`auth-redirect`, forms under `src/components/auth/`).

## Data

- Merge Payload + LiveScore data using existing helpers under `src/lib/` rather than ad-hoc `fetch` in every component.
- Respect caching tags / revalidation patterns already used for the feature you touch.

## Imports

- Use `@/` alias for `src/` imports.
